<Fragment slot="intro">
    <h1>Professional LG Dryer Repair Services in Los Angeles</h1>
    <p>When your LG dryer stops heating or takes three cycles to dry a load of towels, nine times out of ten it's the thermal fuse — but don't grab your toolbox just yet. Our technicians see homeowners in Burbank and Thousand Oaks make this repair worse by installing the wrong fuse rating or missing the lint blockage that caused the original failure.</p>
</Fragment>
<h2>Same-Day LG Dryer Repair Throughout Los Angeles</h2>
<p>We dispatch technicians Monday through Saturday from 8am to 8pm, and our 85% first-visit fix rate means you'll likely have your dryer running before dinner. Our trucks stock OEM parts for every LG series — ThinQ, Signature, DLGX, and DLEX models — because aftermarket components fail within months. The first thing our techs do is run diagnostics on your dryer's sensors and heating elements. Most homeowners don't realize that newer LG models like the ThinQ series have moisture sensors that get coated with fabric softener residue, causing the dryer to shut off early. We clean these sensors properly and test the calibration before moving to mechanical components.</p>
<h3>Licensed Technicians, Not Handymen</h3>
<p>Every technician on our team holds CSLB license #1138898 and receives ongoing LG training. We don't send general repair guys — our techs specialize in LG dryers and know the difference between a bad drum roller and worn drum glides just by listening to the noise your dryer makes.</p>
<h2>Common LG Dryer Problems We Fix Daily</h2>
<p>Lint buildup causes 80% of the service calls we handle, but it's not always where you think. The lint trap catches the obvious stuff, but lint accumulates in the blower housing, exhaust ductwork, and around the heating element. When lint blocks airflow, your dryer overheats and the thermal fuse blows as a safety measure. We've pulled grocery bags worth of lint from dryers that homeowners thought were 'clean' because they emptied the lint trap. Door latch failures happen frequently on DLEX models after about five years — the plastic striker wears down and won't engage the safety switch. Don't try adjusting the door yourself; you'll throw off the seal and create more problems.</p>
<h3>Heating Element Replacements</h3>
<p>LG heating elements burn out gradually, so your dryer might still produce some heat but take forever to finish a cycle. We test element continuity and replace the entire assembly, not just individual coils, because partial heating element failure stresses the remaining coils.</p>
<h3>Control Board Diagnostics</h3>
<p>Modern LG dryers have sophisticated control boards that monitor everything from moisture levels to motor speed. When these boards malfunction, your dryer might start and stop randomly or display error codes. We carry replacement boards for all major LG series and program them on-site.</p>
<h2>Why We Use Only OEM LG Parts</h2>
<p>Aftermarket dryer parts are tempting because they cost less, but they'll leave you calling for another repair within six months. We stock genuine LG components because they're engineered to work with your specific model's sensors, heating elements, and control systems. Generic thermal fuses might have the right amperage rating, but they don't have the proper temperature response curve for LG dryers. When that cheap fuse fails prematurely, it can damage your control board — turning a $20 thermal fuse problem into a $200 control board replacement. Our OEM parts come with manufacturer backing, and we warranty all parts and labor. Most repairs cost between $150-300 depending on the component, but we'll give you an exact quote after diagnosing your dryer.</p>
<h2>Service Coverage and Response Times</h2>
<p>We cover the greater Los Angeles area including Pasadena, with most calls scheduled within 4-6 hours of your phone call. Our diagnostic fee is $65, waived completely when you proceed with the repair. Don't wait until your dryer stops working entirely — call us when you notice longer drying times or unusual noises. Catching problems early prevents more expensive damage to motors and control systems. We've maintained a 4.9-star rating and BBB A+ status by showing up on time and fixing problems right the first time. Our technicians carry tablet-based diagnostic tools that interface directly with LG's service protocols, giving us access to error codes and sensor readings that generic repair companies can't access.</p>
<h3>Emergency Repair Availability</h3>
<p>While we don't charge emergency fees, we understand that some dryer failures create urgent situations. If you have a houseful of wet laundry and houseguests arriving tomorrow, call us anyway — we often squeeze in additional appointments when possible.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>How quickly can you repair my LG dryer?</h3>
<p>Most repairs happen the same day you call, Monday through Saturday. Our technicians carry the most common LG parts on their trucks, so there's an 85% chance we'll complete your repair on the first visit. If we need to order a specialized component like a control board, we'll get your dryer running temporarily if possible and return within 2-3 days with the part.</p>
<h3>What causes LG dryers to stop heating?</h3>
<p>Nine times out of ten, it's a blown thermal fuse caused by restricted airflow. The fuse is a $12 part, but simply replacing it won't fix the underlying problem. Our techs clean out lint buildup in the blower housing and exhaust ducts, then test airflow before installing the new fuse. Without proper cleaning, you'll blow another fuse within weeks.</p>
<h3>Do you warranty your LG dryer repairs?</h3>
<p>We warranty all parts and labor, with warranty periods varying by component type. OEM LG parts typically carry 90-day to 1-year warranties depending on the part. Our labor is warranted for the same period as the part warranty. If the same problem reoccurs during the warranty period, we'll return and fix it at no charge.</p>
<h3>How much does LG dryer repair typically cost?</h3>
<p>Most common repairs run $150-300 including parts and labor. Simple fixes like thermal fuses or door latches are on the lower end, while heating elements or control boards cost more. We charge a $65 diagnostic fee upfront, but waive it completely when you proceed with the repair. No hidden fees or surprise charges.</p>
<h3>Can you fix all LG dryer models?</h3>
<p>We specialize in all LG series including ThinQ, Signature, DLGX, and DLEX models. Our technicians receive ongoing LG training and carry model-specific diagnostic tools. Whether you have a basic stackable unit or a high-end steam dryer, we have the expertise and parts to fix it properly. Older discontinued models might require ordering parts, but we can repair anything LG made in the last 15 years.</p>
